1
00:00:00,495 --> 00:00:07,526
As far as I know these places were not used

2
00:00:07,578 --> 00:00:11,589
As much as those halls upstairs

3
00:00:11,614 --> 00:00:17,526
ISIS used them as detention rooms and cells

4
00:00:17,551 --> 00:00:24,583
To hold opponents and people against the group

5
00:00:24,609 --> 00:00:30,313
Look here these metal parts were not there

6
00:00:30,495 --> 00:00:35,781
They show that ISIS used them as cells and detention rooms

7
00:00:35,806 --> 00:00:37,838
For anyone who opposed

8
00:00:37,863 --> 00:00:45,172
Or anyone who went against ISIS decisions and rulings

9
00:00:48,141 --> 00:00:51,318
Now I remember these were ISIS actions

10
00:00:51,343 --> 00:00:54,365
Interviewer: What were these rooms before?

11
00:00:54,390 --> 00:00:59,963
These rooms were used where Armenian children gathered

12
00:00:59,988 --> 00:01:02,021
And Armenian youth

13
00:01:02,046 --> 00:01:06,318
They were given courses in the Armenian language

14
00:01:06,343 --> 00:01:08,011
So they could preserve their language

15
00:01:08,036 --> 00:01:09,964
And their heritage from disappearing

16
00:01:09,989 --> 00:01:14,677
Especially since there is an Armenian church but that church

17
00:01:14,702 --> 00:01:19,599
Did not host Armenian language lessons

18
00:01:19,624 --> 00:01:25,526
Compared with the Syriac language lessons in other schools

19
00:01:25,551 --> 00:01:31,151
But Armenian language teaching was special and limited to the church

20
00:01:31,176 --> 00:01:35,864
It supervised it and the priest was the one who taught

21
00:01:35,889 --> 00:01:38,963
In cooperation with specialists from the parish

22
00:01:38,988 --> 00:01:42,244
To teach their children Armenian in these halls

23
00:01:42,269 --> 00:01:43,911
Special classrooms
